main event: Three objects in a trail followed a similar object going about 750 mph were observed at 8 miles Northwest of Albuquerque, NM on December 29, 1950.
interesting points: The sighting lasted for about 10-15 minutes., Radar analysis suggests that the sighted objects were likely a balloon., There were previous discussions of UFO activity in the Albuquerque region., The objects were described as traveling at high speed., The report is part of Project 10073 which documents UFO sightings.
sighted object: three unidentified objects in the sky
witness description: Observation made via ground-radar and air-visual methods.
